1.title: Operation Black Biscuit: Infiltrating the Hells Angels
1.plot: ATF agent Jay Dobyns infiltrates the notorious Hell's Angels motorcycle club in the midst of a deadly biker war over drug profits and territory. Dobyns must first pass a series of tests to determine if he's worthy of wearing Angels' colors.

2.title: Operation Cayman: Drug Smuggling on the High Seas
2.plot: South Florida lawman, Jim Sweeting, partners with the DEA to infiltrate a network of drug dealers moving pot and coke via the Cayman Islands. Sweeting leap-frogs from dealer to dealer, busting them one at a time.

3.title: Operation Mr. Untouchable: Dethroning Harlem's Heroin King
3.plot: Nicky Barnes is Harlem's Heroin King. After serving time in jail for drug dealing, Barnes has learned ways to make himself untouchable and his drug empire is such big business that even the President of the United States has taken notice.

4.title: Operation Greylord: Undercover in the Halls of Injustice
4.plot: State prosecutor Terry Hake fulfills a lifelong dream by going undercover for the FBI in Chicago. Hake works tirelessly to expose rampant corruption in the Cook County court system.

5.title: Operation Exeter: Undercover Senior Year
5.plot: Exeter, California is a rural town of 10,000 residents and a thriving high school drug trade. Police officer, Alex Salinas, poses as a high school senior who lands himself in detention to set up drug buys with fellow students.

6.title: Operation Payclip: Bribery in the Big Easy
6.plot: The Port of New Orleans is the stage for an operation aimed at union extortion. FBI agents go undercover to infiltrate the lucrative ship cleaning business of cargo vessels enabled by illegal payments and false paperwork.

7.title: Operation Casablanca: Tracing the Cali Cartel's Cash
7.plot: U.S. Customs spearheads a sting aimed at Mexican bankers laundering money for the Cali and Juarez cartels. Customs sends agent William Gately undercover to infiltrate the financier's ranks, posing as money launderers.

8.title: Operation Iceman: Taking Down the Mafia's Hitman
8.plot: During a volatile period of organized crime, ATF agent Dominick Polifrone assumes the role of a "wise-guy" to gain the confidence of and incriminate the mafia's most prolific hit man, Richard "the Iceman" Kuklinski.

9.title: Operation Pisces: Money Laundering for the Medellin Cartel
9.plot: DEA Agent JD Miller is laundering money for the Medellin cartel. He needs help with the sheer volume of cash pickups so he brings in veteran undercover operative Louis Diaz to manage the West Coast operations.

10.title: Operation Black Coral: Intercepting Caribbean Coke
10.plot: Sarasota detective, Jim Sweeting, infiltrates the vicious Cuban cocaine pipeline controlled by the Medellin cartel. The agent re-invents himself and takes on an alias of a drug trafficker to collect evidence.

11.title: Operation Dead Ringer: Busting Escobar's Cartel
11.plot: Bill Gately and the U.S. Customs Service discover the owner of a coin laundry is laundering large sums of cash through a bank that originates from Columbia. Gately leans that one of the sources of the cash is none other than Pablo Escobar.

12.title: Operation Wake Up Cafe: Betting in Jersey
12.plot: Passaic County, New Jersey officer Julia Torres goes undercover to bust an illegal betting club entrenched in the Little Italy neighborhood.

13.title: Operation Royal Charm: Smuggler's Blues
13.plot: FBI agent Lou Calverese goes undercover to infiltrate the lucrative world of international smuggling. What begins as a case of black market cigarettes soon involves military weapons, $100 dollar counterfeit bills and drugs.

14.title: Operation Nautilus: Pakistani Hash on the High Seas
14.plot: US Customs agent Paul DeCotiis is part of an international undercover plan to intercept 70 tons of Pakistani hashish in the middle of the Pacific Ocean. Customs uses a seizes a boat to meet the traffickers near Midway Island.

15.title: Operation Shattered Shield: Nabbing Dirty Cops
15.plot: FBI agent Juan Jackson goes undercover to build a case against corrupt New Orleans police officers, in the most corrupt city in America. Jackson learns that cops are ripping off street dealers and profiting from the sale of narcotics.

16.title: Operation Chokehold: Busting Boston's Mob
16.plot: FBI agent Vince DelaMontaigne infiltrates the powerful La Cosa Nostra mob in an attempt to break their stranglehold on organized crime in Boston.

17.title: Operation Stolen Bonds
17.plot: Ernie Lijoi is an agent for the Quincy, MA police department, working in tandem with FBI and DEA. An informant tips him off that a crew of bank robbers are looking to sell $800,000 in stolen bonds.

18.title: Operation Shootout: Undercover Attack
18.plot: Nate Hutchinson is part of an undercover team in Ogden, UT while working for the Weber County Sheriff's Department. After years of undercover operations involving small time drug dealing, the team pays a call to an illegal pot grower.

19.title: Operation Straight Arrow: Double Agent Dirty Cop
19.plot: Stanford, Maine detective John Arnold goes undercover to befriend a drug dealer flying in drugs right under their noses.

20.title: Operation 4-U Lounge: Crossroads of Illegal Activity
20.plot: Ken Storch of the Aurora, CO PD infiltrates a local watering hole to tap into the illegal activity operating in plain sight. He takes on a rich kid druggie persona to get inside a local kingpins operation to take him down.

21.title: Operation Luau: Trapping a Dirty Cop
21.plot: Joanne Takasato has no experience in uniform or on the streets of Honolulu. Nevertheless, she works the streets as a small time druggie, making buys before she's assigned the task of taking down a dirty cop.

22.title: Operation Cockfight: Underworld Gambling
22.plot: Stan Sales of the Honolulu PD enters the world of cockfighting, a popular entertainment on the island. Sales and his partners go undercover to videotape and document a local promoter who controls the cockfights.

23.title: Operation Bank Robbery: Breaking the Bank
23.plot: Ken Dye goes undercover for the St. Louis County Sheriff's Department to purchase illegal weapons and hears about a planned bank heist. He is hired to help the would be bank robbers stick up a local bank.

24.title: Operation Canned Tomatoes: Italian Mafia
24.plot: FBI agent Ron Moretti enters the dangerous world of the Italian mafia, while investigating the supply of heroin into the US. Moretti devises a plan to have the mafia ship their white powder inside canned tomatoes.

25.title: Operation Searchlight: White Supremacist Heist
25.plot: Mike McCommas acts as point man to the FBI's case against the Arizona Patriots, a white supremacist group. McCommas discovers that the gang is plotting an armored car heist.

26.title: Operation Scam Artist: Arson for Hire
26.plot: Free-lance undercover detective Bob Cerrone is hired by a Denver insurance company to investigate a series of insurance claims.

27.title: Operation Con Cinco: Rocky Mountain High
27.plot: Denver cop Joe Padilla infiltrates a thriving drug crew in the center of the Rocky Mountains. Padilla is nearly shot during one exchange but continues to do deals as he goes up the drug dealing food chain.

28.title: Operation Missouri 500: Dogfight Duo
28.plot: Jeff Heath of the Missouri Highway Patrol takes on the alias of a dog fighting breeder to infiltrate the horrific and violent world of illegal dog fighting.

29.title: Operation Thin Crust: Destroying the Vegas Mob
29.plot: FBI agent Charlie Maurer partners with a mob hit man to penetrate the Vegas mafia. Maurer uses the hit man as a Trojan horse and they form a tenuous alliance to gather evidence against the hit man's former partners in crime.

30.title: Operation Orozco: Cartel Laundry
30.plot: FBI agent Ed Guillen goes undercover as a banker to cozy up with a Columbian cartel member and help launder his dirty cash. Guillen launders millions while taping incriminating conversations that will eventually convict the drug king pin.

31.title: Operation Lockdown: Imprisoned Cop Killer
31.plot: FBI agent Steve Salmieri takes on the alias of a mob hit man to go inside a prison to get evidence against a cop killer who is incarcerated on another charge.

32.title: Operation Komex: Selling Sarin
32.plot: US Customs agent Rick Kennan masquerades as a weapons dealer to get inside a Korean arms operation that's soliciting military secrets and weapons.

33.title: Operation Diablos: Two Wheel Traffickers
33.plot: FBI agent Mark Pocoro is picked to infiltrate the Diablos motorcycle gang, who are deeply involved in various criminal activities from drugs to stolen cars.

34.title: Operation Vinnie the Plumber: Defusing a Bomber
34.plot: When a bomb is detonated under a police car, ATF agent Vince Cefalu goes undercover to get the suspect. Cefalu becomes a disgruntled dirt bag and hires the bomber to build him some bombs.

35.title: Operation Citizens Band: CB Trojan Horse
35.plot: Quincy, MA cop Ernie Lijoi goes undercover to take down an enterprising drug dealer who is renting out weapons to other criminals. To get inside this gang of dirt bags, Ernie becomes Mr. Fix It, with a flair for installing CB radios.

36.title: Operation Grey Sunset: Montana Freemen
36.plot: FBI Special Agent Tim Healy infiltrates a dangerous anti-government group called the Montana Freemen who are running a scam to bilk the IRS out of millions to fund their planned Armageddon.

37.title: Operation Nevada Volunteers: Sin City Bomber
37.plot: ATF agent Jay Dobyns infiltrates the dirt-bag ranks of the Nevada Volunteers, a pack of losers plotting to overthrow the government. During his infiltration of the group, Jay discovers one member intends to blow up the Vegas strip.

38.title: Operation Last Call: Hooker Takedown
38.plot: Memphis Police officer Anthony Godwin goes undercover in the seedy adult nightclub scene to break up organized crime involving drugs and prostitution.

39.title: Operation Gambling Rings
39.plot: FBI agent Vince Delamontagne infiltrates the New England La Cosa Nostro mob that controls gambling and drugs in New England. Passaic County, NJ deputy Julia Torres opens an illegal betting club to snare local wise guys.

40.title: Operation Dead Game: Dogfighting Takedown
40.plot: Houston cops Cliff Manning and Scott Davis go undercover to infiltrate a group of black dog-fighters making money hand over fist. They open a dog pen club with hidden audio and video cameras to get evidence.

41.title: Operation Shamrock: Carolina Militia
41.plot: FBI agent John Osa uses his skill as a financial crimes expert to befriend the leader of a Carolina militia. The mastermind of the anti-government group is using fraud and a Ponzi scheme to fund his operation.

42.title: Operation Tropical Storm: Japanese Meth Ring
42.plot: FBI agent Jim Stern uses his bi-racial heritage and command of Japanese to infiltrate the notorious Yakuza mob that's smuggling drugs into Hawaii. Jim's target is a tattoo covered hit man.

43.title: Operation Violent Outlaws
43.plot: FBI agent Marc Pocoro infiltrates the Diablos motorcycle gang involved in drugs and stolen cars. But along the way, he's made as a cop.

44.title: Operation Rooster: Aryan Brotherhood
44.plot: DEA agents Jay Dobyns and Louis Quinonez are sent to infiltrate the Aryan Brotherhood gang, to take down a bomb making operation. But while the duo builds a case against the bomb maker, they stumble upon a murder.

45.title: Operation Shi Ron: Corrupt Cops
45.plot: FBI agent Herman Groman takes on the dangerous assignment of infiltrating crooked cops in Cleveland, Ohio. Herman sets up an illegal gambling operation to snare the cops who offer him protection.

46.title: Operation Drug Cartels
46.plot: Saratoga, FL agent Jim Sweeting sails the Caribbean to infiltrate the Cayman cartel drug operation. US Customs supervisor Bill Gately uncovers a can of worms with the Mexican banking system, that's bankrolling South American cartels.

47.title: Operation Rollo Tomasi: Kaika Klan Outlaws
47.plot: FBI agent Jim Nice partners with the Akron Police to target the Kaika Klan Outlaws, a black street gang that's terrorizing the city. But Jim is white, and this won't be a cake walk.

48.title: Operation End of Days: Meth Eradication
48.plot: When Independence, Missouri cop Steve Cook stumbles upon a meth lab, an undercover operation is launched with Steve as the point men. Problem is, Independence is a small town and Steve gets getting made as a cop.

49.title: Operation Catwalk: Strip Club Sting
49.plot: FBI agent John Tanza goes undercover targeting the Cleveland mob the best way he can-by running a strip club that they call home. But rival factions place John squarely in the middle of the turf war.

50.title: Operation Mobster
50.plot: DEA agent Louis Diaz builds a case against New York's most notorious drug mastermind, Nicky Barnes. ATF agent Dominick Polifrone cozies up to a monster serial killer, Richard "Iceman" Kuklinski and nearly becomes a victim.

51.title: Operation Link Bet: Vegas Mob Bust
51.plot: FBI agent John Ligato is on a mission to drive a stake into the heart of the Vegas mob. To do this, he cozies up to a mafia boss who has his hands in organized crime. John infiltrates a mob trucking heist ring.

52.title: Operation Big Easy, New Orleans Mob
52.plot: FBI agent Geoff Santini goes undercover to snag a drug-dealing killer. Geoff endures weeks of dinners and business meetings while the dealer decides if he's dealing with a cop, or the real deal.

imdb.title: Deep Undercover
plot: _Deep Undercover_ (qv) is a true crimes series from writer and producer Joe Pistone, the real "Donnie Brasco." Each episode tells the story of a different undercover operation from the POV of the undercover officers involved.
